cs.SI, cs.SOC, cs.DS, cs.CYBER, cs.LG

The paper deals with the analysis of diffusion processes in social contacts and the development of applications using graph models. This suggests that the paper could belong to the sub-categories of Social and Information Networks (cs.SI), Social and Behavioral Sciences (cs.SOC), Data Structures and Algorithms (cs.DS), Cybersecurity and Privacy (cs.CYBER), and Machine Learning (cs.LG). However, since the paper focuses on the development of a graph model to capture indirect interactions among individuals, cs.SI and cs.SOC are the most likely sub-categories. The other sub-categories are also possible as they are related to the analysis of data and the development of models.
